1
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:42,560
You should've laid low and behaved yourself when I let you live.

2
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:43,600
(Episode 7)

3
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:09,240
What's happening? Why can't I get out of here?

4
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,200
What is going on?

5
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:13,160
Why can't I get out of here?

6
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:34,560
Gosh, who was it?

7
00:01:35,039 --> 00:01:36,479
I clearly saw it.

8
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:43,720
By the way, where did Joon go?

9
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:56,520
Why can't I get out?

10
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,080
Why can't I...

11
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,240
get out of this body?

12
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:25,400
Joon, were you here the whole time?

13
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,520
I looked everywhere for you.

14
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:35,680
Actually, there's something urgent.

15
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,200
When the power went out earlier,

16
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,000
I saw a moment of death.

17
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:44,520
It might've been an abduction case. The person was tied to a chair.

18
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,880
Then the building exploded.

19
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:50,040
Why did that girl pop into my mind when I was about to die?

20
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:53,200
I can't understand it. How unpleasant.

21
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:55,480
Joon.

22
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,920
Joon, you're listening, right?

23
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:00,960
Yes.

24
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:02,920
What about Leo?

25
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:05,640
I checked right away, but it wasn't him.

26
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:08,280
I checked people around him, and I don't think it's them either.

27
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:11,480
I have no idea who it was.

28
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,600
I'll get out soon. Give me a minute.

29
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:29,440
Someone will die.

30
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,560
I'm tired. Let's leave.

31
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:48,600
This is crazy. I must've lost my mind.

32
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:51,240
She's really not my type.

33
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:53,920
Hey, Mr. Green.

34
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:57,400
It looks like Joe Black is abducting Princess Green.

35
00:03:57,760 --> 00:03:59,640
Will you let him leave with her, Mr. Green?

36
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:01,960
Cut it out, okay?

37
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:04,320
Gosh, you're making me feel embarrassed.

38
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:07,400
What's the matter with you? I was just joking.

39
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,120
Hey, why are you drinking so much?

40
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:10,600
You'll black out again.

41
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:14,440
You don't remember a thing when you black out.

42
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,760
Stop drinking. You'll make a mistake.

43
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,200
Let go. Hey!

44
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:56,440
That shadow...

45
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,720
Who could it be?

46
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,960
They're never around when I need them.

47
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,080
Why aren't they back yet?

48
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:15,120
Why are you getting back just now?

49
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:17,280
Why are you welcoming us so enthusiastically?

50
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:19,680
You must have a hidden agenda.

51
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:22,360
Come on! You better tell us the facts.

52
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,480
It's "truth".

53
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:25,240
- It's "facts". - It's "truth".

54
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:27,200
- "Facts". - Be quiet. Listen up, guys.

55
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,960
I can't get out. I cannot get out of this body.

56
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:33,120
What? What do you mean?

57
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:35,320
Look at this.

58
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:38,320
This body fell into a river and died after some jerk stabbed me.

59
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:41,000
I'm certain that it died. It fell into a river and died.

60
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,040
But I couldn't get out of it.

61
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:45,040
That's why it's alive again now. Does this make sense to you?

62
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:47,680
Gosh, no way.

63
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,880
416.

64
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,480
Do I look like I'm lying now?

65
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,640
Do I? Look at me.

66
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:59,800
What are you doing now? Are you trying to poop or what?

67
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:08,320
I can't get out. I can't leave this body.

68
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:11,280
Sorry? We can go in and out of human bodies freely...

69
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:13,040
after entering them.

70
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:16,160
Exactly. But I can't get out of this body.

71
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:18,560
No matter how hard I try, I just can't leave this body.

72
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:23,200
007, why is this happening? Say something.

73
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,720
Well, I'm not sure.

74
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:28,920
I've never been through anything like this even in the Joseon era.

75
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,400
Then hurry up, and look into it.

76
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:33,040
Find out why this is happening to me, would you?

77
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:35,040
What if I can't get out of this body even after catching that loser?

78
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,200
I'll be doomed.

79
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:37,600
Okay, I heard you.

80
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:41,120
But try to look at the bright side.

81
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:43,440
As long as you're locked up in that body,

82
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:47,760
it'll be invincible and immortal no matter how many times...

83
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:51,040
that jerk who's after Han Moo Gang tries to kill him.

84
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:55,480
That means you'll be able to continue using his body.

85
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,760
- Really? - Yes.

86
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:01,440
Am I supposed to be happy about this or what?

87
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:09,320
Why did you kill Han Moo Gang?

88
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:10,400
I'm sorry.

89
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:12,880
I lost my reason momentarily.

90
00:07:13,520 --> 00:07:17,280
If we kill Han Moo Gang, that jerk won't let it slide!

91
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:18,880
I'll make sure there are no further problems.

92
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:22,720
And I'll take care of the body before it gets found.

93
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:37,920
You didn't have to kill Moo Gang!

94
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:43,640
Shut it before I rip your mouth off.

95
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,520
It's me.

96
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:51,880
What happened to the informant tailing Moo Gang?

97
00:07:54,159 --> 00:07:55,159
Still?

98
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:59,560
The situation is quite urgent now. Find that jerk immediately.

99
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:17,640
What?

100
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,160
Why am I here?

101
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:22,720
I'm supposed to be in Ha Ram's storage.

102
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:24,640
- Side effects? - That's right.

103
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:27,960
You might not be able to teleport as you please.

104
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:29,600
I can't teleport? Why not?

105
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:33,760
You have dreams now. That means you're becoming more and more human.

106
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:36,760
Humans cannot teleport, can they?

107
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,440
What is this?

108
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,600
Am I really becoming a human?

109
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:44,840
I won't be able to get out of this body or teleport.

110
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,400
Han Moo Gang's body is gone? What do you mean?

111
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,560
Have you looked everywhere?

112
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:55,320
Search the bottom of the lake if you have to!

113
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,320
These idiots.

114
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:08,920
What?

115
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:11,080
He's not dead.

116
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:16,720
I'm busy, but I have to walk like those stupid humans?

117
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:25,200
Isn't this a car key?

118
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:30,160
That's right.

119
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:31,520
Where is it?

120
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,960
Yes, this is it.

121
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,960
All right.

122
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:51,600
I've spent ages in cars waiting to take those who die in car accidents.

123
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:54,200
This will be a piece of cake.

124
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,560
Where is the key?

125
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,720
Where should I put it in?

126
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:06,840
There.

127
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,800
Good. Oh, gosh.

128
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:15,000
I can do this.

129
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:20,320
I can do this. Of course I can.

130
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:52,680
Hello?

131
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:57,800
What?

132
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:00,040
My dad?

133
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:02,000
Yes. Okay.

134
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:10,240
Yes, I just got here. Where should I go?

135
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:27,840
That man...

136
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:31,680
- Hey! - Just die! Die already, please!

137
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,520
Let go of me!

138
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,720
Ms. Fortune-teller.

139
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:39,680
Hurry!

140
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:42,080
Hurry up!

141
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,600
What do you think?

142
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:51,600
Do you see it?

143
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:59,360
Hey, you brat.

144
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:01,920
I told you to never come here.

145
00:12:01,920 --> 00:12:03,600
What... What are you doing?

146
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:05,120
Who are you?

147
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:10,840
Get off me!

148
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:13,240
Are you okay?

149
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:15,360
Let's go.

150
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,720
Why that little...

151
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,200
Hi, Lawyer Jung.

152
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:30,880
Did you copy it?

153
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:34,600
Bring it to my office.

154
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:47,120
The person who killed that man was wearing the same watch.

155
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,800
Does that mean the person who will kill that man...

156
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,280
will kill Mr. Oh's dad as well?

157
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:55,200
Listen.

158
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:04,640
Don't be so discouraged. Let's wait a little longer.

159
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:07,960
He has survived crises worse than this.

160
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:15,440
- Hello. - Okay then.

161
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,920
- What is it? - It's about Yoon Soo Wan.

162
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:21,240
She handed in her resignation, and I can't reach her. What's going on?

163
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,200
She... She handed in her resignation?

164
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,840
You didn't know about this? Here.

165
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:29,320
(Letter of Resignation)

166
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,000
Hold on.

167
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:38,520
The phone is turned off...

168
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:41,360
Her phone is off.

169
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,160
What happened to her?

170
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:52,240
Did the man who was here leave?

171
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:55,080
You mean that grump? He left earlier.

172
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:58,440
- Where is her other guardian? - She didn't come here today.

173
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:06,960
(Kim Soon Hee)

174
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:16,920
She must've seen something again.

175
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:22,120
I told her not to get involved in it.

176
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:23,680
Please help me this once.

177
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:27,640
I told you. I can't give you the patient's personal information.

178
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:31,200
What should I do?

179
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:37,320
Listen. You can give it to a police officer, right?

180
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:47,680
What?

181
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:51,360
So please come to Royeol Hospital now, and check it for me.

182
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,520
Hello? Hello...

183
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:57,360
There she goes again. It wasn't easy for me to come this far!

184
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:18,600
Have you seen someone wearing a watch...

185
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:21,360
with a butterfly shape around your dad?

186
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:24,040
I'm not sure.

187
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,200
I should call the police.

188
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:27,960
No one would believe me.

189
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:30,800
What should we do then?

190
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:32,040
Don't worry too much.

191
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:35,240
There will be a way to catch the killer.

192
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:38,360
- But... But how? - Before...

193
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:42,480
he kills your dad,

194
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:45,360
he will kill someone else first.

195
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:47,400
- What? - It's the husband...

196
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,440
of a patient in this hospital.

197
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:53,000
I saw the killer stabbing him to death.

198
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,520
How can you be sure it's the same person?

199
00:15:58,240 --> 00:15:59,560
You said you didn't see his face.

200
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:02,800
His watch. He was wearing the same watch.

201
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:04,920
But...

202
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:07,400
that can't be the only watch of its' kind.

203
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:10,040
The bloodstain he got on his watch when he killed the husband...

204
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:12,400
was still there...

205
00:16:12,920 --> 00:16:16,320
when he was removing your dad's respirator.

206
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,160
There may be many watches which look alike,

207
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:23,280
but the bloodstain can't be the same, can it?

208
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,440
So there is still a chance.

209
00:16:27,640 --> 00:16:31,080
If we catch the killer before he kills the husband,

210
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:34,080
your dad may be fine as well.

211
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,240
So if we catch him when he tries...

212
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:38,480
to kill the husband...

213
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:40,920
Then my dad won't die either.

214
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:45,240
- Who would try to kill those two? - I don't know.

215
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,440
Did you find out?

216
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:51,720
His phone is turned off. This is his address.

217
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:54,080
Let's hurry up and go.

218
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:55,920
What?

219
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:57,320
Let go of me.

220
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:59,320
How persistent.

221
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:01,360
You're such a nosy person.

222
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:02,920
You hold my hand whenever you want.

223
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:05,520
Fine, I won't hold your hand. Let's hurry off.

224
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:07,119
Wait. Let me come with you.

225
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:09,040
You should stay here.

226
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:11,040
Don't leave your dad's side,

227
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:14,040
and call me if someone comes to your mind.

228
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:23,000
Don't worry too much. We'll catch the killer.

229
00:17:24,119 --> 00:17:27,520
- Thank you. - What are you doing? I'm busy.

230
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:36,040
Hello?

231
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:57,840
(Moojin Time Mart collapsed.)

232
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:06,960
(Honorary Graduation, Park Seung Chul)

233
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:14,160
Seung Chul?

234
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:22,960
Ha Ram!

235
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:24,680
Seung Chul.

236
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:28,760
Did Joon write you back?

237
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:34,560
He must be busy trying to get accustomed to Seoul.

238
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:37,920
Are you wearing that again because Joon isn't around?

239
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:40,360
He told you not to cover your pretty eyes.

240
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:41,960
Take it off.

241
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:49,040
I’m going to tell him everything if you wear them again.

242
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:51,920
Gosh, I might be late. See you!

243
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:55,000
Seung Chul! The shadow...

244
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:57,000
The shadow...

245
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:08,400
Ha Ram, what's wrong? Are you feeling sick?

246
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:11,640
Don't... Don't go. Don't go to the movies.

247
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:12,640
What?

248
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:16,640
Are you talking about going to the movies as a group tomorrow?

249
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:18,600
Tomorrow? Is it tomorrow?

250
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:21,120
Don't... Don't go. Please don't go there.

251
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:23,480
Hey, Seung Chul.

252
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:25,400
The school bell rings

253
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,560
Our class is about to start

254
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:30,400
If we're late, we'll get in trouble

255
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:33,520
All right, Hyun Soo. Let's go together.

256
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:37,160
Don't... Don't go. Don't go there.

257
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:39,120
Okay, I won't go to the movies.

258
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:41,520
You should get going. I'll go now.

259
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,200
Seung Chul!

260
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:44,760
What's the matter with that kid?

261
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:46,560
It's nothing.

262
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,200
Back then,

263
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:54,160
I was too young.

264
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:56,880
I should’ve held on to you more tightly.

265
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,400
I should've tried harder to make sure you didn't go there.

266
00:20:03,080 --> 00:20:04,240
Is it someone you know?

267
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:15,120
Back in elementary school,

268
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:18,880
he was your closest friend.

269
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:21,040
Me?

270
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:25,240
He was my friend?

