00:37:01,160 --> 00:37:02,800
It's all over now, right?

532
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:06,520
Seung Chul's dad and Mr. Oh's dad will both be fine, right?

533
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:08,920
Probably. That punk has been arrested.

534
00:37:10,320 --> 00:37:13,120
But still, I should see him to be at ease.

535
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:16,160
Stop talking nonsense.

536
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:17,880
Let's go now.

537
00:37:24,120 --> 00:37:25,160
Hello?

538
00:37:25,160 --> 00:37:27,120
I'm calling from Royeol Hospital.

539
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:29,840
You told me to call when the patient's guardian came.

540
00:37:30,040 --> 00:37:31,680
He's in the hospital room right now.

541
00:37:57,240 --> 00:37:58,760
(World Drink)

542
00:38:00,880 --> 00:38:03,720
(World Drink)

543
00:38:03,960 --> 00:38:05,160
Get off.

544
00:38:05,160 --> 00:38:06,720
What do you think you're doing?

545
00:38:07,280 --> 00:38:08,640
It was him.

546
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:11,520
Hey, Ha Ram.

547
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:14,800
You might cross paths, so I'll just wait here and check if he comes out.

548
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:17,800
Call me right away if you see Seung Chul's dad.

549
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:30,040
What?

550
00:38:31,440 --> 00:38:33,040
Is this guy really the culprit?

551
00:38:36,240 --> 00:38:37,640
How annoying.

552
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:42,760
You thief!

553
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:48,560
Oh, you're Detective Han. What are you doing here?

554
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:50,440
This...

555
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:53,800
I'm sorry. I wasn't planning on stealing it at first.

556
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:55,000
What?

557
00:38:56,080 --> 00:38:58,480
You stole it? Isn't this yours?

558
00:38:58,600 --> 00:39:03,120
No. I went to that house because I had to find something.

559
00:39:13,120 --> 00:39:14,240
Is anyone home?

560
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:29,760
I'm really telling the truth. Please forgive me just this once.

561
00:39:30,560 --> 00:39:32,560
If he's not the owner of this watch,

562
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:35,040
does that mean someone else is the murderer?

563
00:39:53,480 --> 00:39:56,480
Are you still looking for the owner of this watch and the man who...

564
00:39:56,480 --> 00:39:57,960
made Han Jin Sook work as a prostitute?

565
00:39:58,080 --> 00:40:00,520
That's why I'm going to Moojin today.

566
00:40:00,520 --> 00:40:04,440
Some of the prostitutes who used to work with Han Jin Sook...

567
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:07,040
are apparently still living in Moojin.

568
00:40:07,040 --> 00:40:10,040
My gosh, you guys are working so hard.

569
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:12,120
- Did you eat? - What took you so long?

570
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:13,720
Eat this while you work.

571
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:15,680
- What's that? - I got it from a famous restaurant.

572
00:40:15,680 --> 00:40:17,240
Oh, really? Thank you.

573
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:21,920
What are you doing? Why did you just act that way?

574
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:30,120
I think he wants to take Han Jin Sook's case from us.

575
00:40:31,080 --> 00:40:33,440
- What? - I overheard him while sleeping.

576
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:36,960
But he was searching Han Jin Sook's phone call records.

577
00:40:36,960 --> 00:40:41,040
And when we were having a team meeting, I saw him...

578
00:40:41,040 --> 00:40:43,760
trying to eavesdrop on what we were saying.

579
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:47,200
Exactly. He's just trying to take this case from us...

580
00:40:47,200 --> 00:40:49,040
because he's not getting anywhere...

581
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:51,800
with that mental hospital case.

582
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:55,160
So keep things confidential if you don't want to lose our case to him.

583
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:58,520
Our team will no longer exist if we lose this case as well. Okay?

584
00:40:58,520 --> 00:40:59,560
Okay.

585
00:41:03,640 --> 00:41:04,640
Why?

586
00:41:05,360 --> 00:41:06,440
What?

587
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:11,960
My gosh.

588
00:41:12,560 --> 00:41:16,280
That jerk used to wash my socks when he was a recruit.

589
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:18,880
My gosh.

590
00:41:19,200 --> 00:41:20,880
- Let's go. - Okay.

591
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:22,200
Keep up the good work.

592
00:41:23,720 --> 00:41:26,240
- Hey, you can eat this. - Okay. Thank you.

593
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:29,920
- Bye. - Where's Moo Gang?

594
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:33,680
Him? My gosh, don't even talk to me about him.

595
00:41:33,680 --> 00:41:36,120
I can't even look at him anymore.

596
00:41:37,280 --> 00:41:38,720
Actually, I'm relieved.

597
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:42,280
I'm going to think of him as a freelancer for a while.

598
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:43,560
That's what I'm going to do.

599
00:41:44,640 --> 00:41:45,960
Okay, go ahead.

600
00:41:48,160 --> 00:41:49,800
Think whatever you want.

601
00:41:58,320 --> 00:42:00,640
No one seems to know anything about what happened to Moo Gang.

602
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:03,120
I'll continue to keep an eye on them.

603
00:42:03,880 --> 00:42:06,640
So don't show up in front of Moo Gang for a while.

604
00:42:06,960 --> 00:42:08,000
Okay.

605
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:14,160
I'm pretty sure that jerk saw my face.

606
00:42:14,160 --> 00:42:16,760
Why didn't he report me even after he got stabbed?

607
00:42:29,120 --> 00:42:31,680
(World Drink)

608
00:42:31,680 --> 00:42:33,400
(Sunglasses)

609
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:34,520
Hello?

610
00:42:34,560 --> 00:42:36,840
Didn't you see Seung Chul's dad leaving?

611
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:38,000
They say he left just now.

612
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:39,160
No, I didn't see him.

613
00:42:45,400 --> 00:42:48,320
We already caught the culprit,

614
00:42:48,720 --> 00:42:50,280
so I'm sure nothing will happen.

615
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:52,560
Ms. Fortune-teller.

616
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:54,840
I heard that Pastor Kang turned out to be the culprit.

617
00:42:55,680 --> 00:42:58,800
I also handed in my dad's donation records to the police.

618
00:43:00,200 --> 00:43:01,200
That ungrateful jerk.

619
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:04,720
Now that we caught him, does that mean my dad's going to live?

620
00:43:04,880 --> 00:43:06,400
Yes, but...

621
00:43:08,480 --> 00:43:10,440
Why didn't I think of that earlier?

622
00:43:11,360 --> 00:43:12,840
We can just check and see...

623
00:43:12,840 --> 00:43:15,840
if there's still a shadow on your father's body or not.

624
00:43:33,560 --> 00:43:35,720
It seems that Pastor Kang wasn't the culprit.

625
00:43:35,720 --> 00:43:38,240
- What? - What's going on?

626
00:43:38,240 --> 00:43:40,680
If Pastor Kang isn't the culprit, that means he'll be in trouble too.

627
00:43:47,480 --> 00:43:48,480
Wait for me.

628
00:43:48,480 --> 00:43:50,120
(Office, World Drink)

629
00:43:51,640 --> 00:43:52,760
Good work.

630
00:43:52,760 --> 00:43:54,240
Thank you, sir.

631
00:43:55,320 --> 00:43:56,360
What is it?

632
00:43:56,360 --> 00:43:58,160
Didn't Mr. Yang tell you off for being late?

633
00:43:58,160 --> 00:44:00,480
Everything was fine.

634
00:44:00,480 --> 00:44:02,440
- I'll go home now. - Okay. Goodbye.

635
00:44:02,440 --> 00:44:03,600
- Bye. - Bye.

636
00:44:21,120 --> 00:44:22,520
I guess she found out.

637
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:26,000
But you won't be able to save anyone...

638
00:44:26,720 --> 00:44:28,720
because I'm not going to let you.

639
00:44:28,920 --> 00:44:31,200
I'm 444, the best there is in this business.

640
00:44:32,640 --> 00:44:35,560
What? Wait. Right here.

641
00:44:36,480 --> 00:44:38,200
Why didn't he see him?

642
00:44:43,560 --> 00:44:44,680
Wait.

643
00:44:47,200 --> 00:44:48,240
That's...

644
00:44:57,560 --> 00:45:00,320
Turn on the lights. We need to turn the lights on!

645
00:45:03,960 --> 00:45:05,480
I almost forgot.

646
00:45:05,480 --> 00:45:06,600
About what?

647
00:45:07,400 --> 00:45:08,720
When there was a blackout...

648
00:45:09,040 --> 00:45:12,280
at the party, I saw a shadow.

649
00:45:12,640 --> 00:45:13,720
What?

650
00:45:13,760 --> 00:45:15,920
I couldn't see the person's face because it was too dark.

651
00:45:16,360 --> 00:45:19,560
But that person had a mask on and was kidnapped.

652
00:45:19,560 --> 00:45:22,520
And that coat was also at the scene.

653
00:45:22,520 --> 00:45:25,680
What does that man have anything to do with kidnapping?

654
00:45:27,400 --> 00:45:29,280
What? He's the guy...

655
00:45:29,920 --> 00:45:31,720
who delivered alcohol to the party.

656
00:45:32,760 --> 00:45:34,400
- What? - I remember...

657
00:45:34,400 --> 00:45:35,400
because I signed the receipt myself.

658
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:40,360
Yes. It was from World Drink.

659
00:45:41,280 --> 00:45:42,640
Mr. Park?

660
00:45:42,680 --> 00:45:44,960
He just left after bringing back his truck.

661
00:45:46,320 --> 00:45:47,560
What's this?

662
00:45:47,920 --> 00:45:49,640
My gosh, this startled me.

663
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:51,320
What is this?

664
00:45:53,640 --> 00:45:55,120
What? That's...

665
00:46:01,760 --> 00:46:03,600
He's Steven Yoo.

666
00:46:04,440 --> 00:46:05,440
Hi, man.

667
00:46:05,440 --> 00:46:06,720
What's this doing here?

668
00:47:01,320 --> 00:47:04,840
When the power went out earlier, I saw a moment of death.

669
00:47:05,320 --> 00:47:08,160
It might've been an abduction case. The person was tied to a chair.

670
00:47:08,880 --> 00:47:10,400
Then the building exploded.

671
00:47:10,480 --> 00:47:11,480
What?

672
00:47:13,040 --> 00:47:14,720
Was that guy the kidnapper?

673
00:47:17,640 --> 00:47:20,520
Sang Min. This is what your friend was wearing at the party, right?

674
00:47:20,520 --> 00:47:21,920
That's Steven's.

675
00:47:22,520 --> 00:47:23,880
Why do you have this?

676
00:47:23,880 --> 00:47:25,680
- Call him right now. - Okay.

677
00:47:29,880 --> 00:47:31,680
The receiver's phone is turned off.

678
00:47:32,160 --> 00:47:33,360
His phone has been turned off.

679
00:47:34,880 --> 00:47:38,120
When was the last time you saw him?

680
00:47:38,120 --> 00:47:40,040
I think he left in the middle of the party.

681
00:47:40,280 --> 00:47:42,960
I guess he thought it was boring. He didn't even say goodbye.

682
00:47:43,160 --> 00:47:44,440
Do you know where he lives?

683
00:47:44,960 --> 00:47:47,160
Yes. He lives in the Philippines.

684
00:47:47,160 --> 00:47:49,640
And right now, he's staying at a hotel in Seoul.

685
00:47:50,160 --> 00:47:51,240
He is staying there with his mom.

686
00:48:01,360 --> 00:48:04,200
Why are you doing this? Why...

687
00:48:04,840 --> 00:48:05,840
Shut it!

688
00:48:06,040 --> 00:48:07,440
You should resent your father.

689
00:48:07,760 --> 00:48:08,960
Shut it!

690
00:48:12,680 --> 00:48:14,560
Please... Please...

691
00:48:14,880 --> 00:48:16,080
Help!

692
00:48:23,480 --> 00:48:25,880
Is your son really safe?

693
00:48:25,880 --> 00:48:28,240
He already left Korea to go to school.

694
00:48:28,720 --> 00:48:31,600
Who are you to ask me questions about him?

695
00:48:32,120 --> 00:48:34,520
If you don't leave, I'm going to call the police.

696
00:48:34,520 --> 00:48:37,160
Why did you come to Korea?

697
00:48:37,520 --> 00:48:38,920
Why are you here?

698
00:48:38,920 --> 00:48:43,000
We had a Korean housekeeper who took care of Steven as a child.

699
00:48:43,320 --> 00:48:46,240
But she had to come back to Korea because she got into an accident.

700
00:48:46,360 --> 00:48:49,840
We came to visit her because my son got worried about her.

701
00:48:53,960 --> 00:48:55,400
There's no record of him having left Korea.

702
00:48:56,120 --> 00:48:57,400
Why are you lying?

703
00:48:58,480 --> 00:49:00,320
You have to tell us the truth.

704
00:49:01,120 --> 00:49:03,120
Your son's life is on the line.

705
00:49:04,040 --> 00:49:06,880
Your son got kidnapped, right?

706
00:49:07,400 --> 00:49:09,400
The kidnapper called you, didn't he?

707
00:49:10,520 --> 00:49:13,360
It's Mr. Park Soon Nam, right?

708
00:49:13,600 --> 00:49:14,880
You know who he is, don't you?

709
00:49:14,880 --> 00:49:16,280
No!

710
00:49:17,680 --> 00:49:19,520
I have nothing more to say to you.

711
00:49:20,240 --> 00:49:21,880
So get out of here right now.

712
00:49:22,560 --> 00:49:25,320
Excuse me. Wait. Please.

713
00:49:29,160 --> 00:49:31,160
Mr. Park is going to die soon.

714
00:49:31,680 --> 00:49:34,840
I think he has something to do with this incident.

715
00:49:35,400 --> 00:49:37,560
I wonder why he kidnapped Steven.

716
00:49:37,680 --> 00:49:40,520
Maybe it's because of money. Sang Min told me that...

717
00:49:41,120 --> 00:49:44,720
she raises Steven all by himself, and she's apparently really rich.

718
00:49:45,880 --> 00:49:49,040
If he just wanted money, he would've tried to kill him quietly.

719
00:49:49,040 --> 00:49:52,240
He wouldn't be making such a big issue by installing bombs.

720
00:49:52,680 --> 00:49:54,080
Then I wonder if he's trying to take revenge.

721
00:49:54,560 --> 00:49:56,320
We need to catch him first.

722
00:49:56,320 --> 00:49:58,280
Should we go back to the hospital? He might've gone back again.

723
00:50:11,320 --> 00:50:12,400
It's me.

724
00:50:12,560 --> 00:50:16,240
Some people came and asked me questions about Steven.

725
00:50:16,960 --> 00:50:18,080
What should I do?

726
00:51:28,640 --> 00:51:29,800
What's this?

727
00:51:34,200 --> 00:51:35,280
(Sunglasses)

728
00:51:40,560 --> 00:51:41,600
Who are you?

729
00:51:41,920 --> 00:51:43,640
Why are you following me?

730
00:51:44,760 --> 00:51:45,760
Calm down.

731
00:51:52,240 --> 00:51:54,280
Who are you? What are you?

732
00:52:00,400 --> 00:52:03,680
I warned her that her son's going to die if she tells the police.

733
00:52:04,480 --> 00:52:06,360
I can't believe she still called the police.

734
00:52:07,320 --> 00:52:10,040
Calm down. You might really stab me.

735
00:52:10,360 --> 00:52:12,440
How do you expect me to calm down?

736
00:52:13,040 --> 00:52:14,560
I'm going to kill you too.

737
00:52:22,000 --> 00:52:23,520
I said calm down.

738
00:52:23,520 --> 00:52:25,680
I don't care if you kill anyone or even decide to kill yourself.

739
00:52:25,680 --> 00:52:28,080
You can do whatever you want.

740
00:52:38,760 --> 00:52:39,840
This is...

741
00:52:51,080 --> 00:52:54,000
I'll go to the reception desk and ask if he came by.

742
00:53:07,760 --> 00:53:09,920
Is Ms. Kim Soon Hee's guardian not here?

743
00:53:09,920 --> 00:53:12,200
I think he went somewhere for a while.

744
00:53:12,200 --> 00:53:14,320
I already told him that she needs to get an MRI scan today.

745
00:53:14,960 --> 00:53:16,960
Please tell him if he gets here while she's gone.

746
00:53:17,840 --> 00:53:20,040
It'll take around 30 minutes.

747
00:53:48,280 --> 00:53:49,400
This person...

748
00:53:51,000 --> 00:53:53,000
Why do you have this?

749
00:53:53,120 --> 00:53:54,400
Who does it belong to?

750
00:53:55,880 --> 00:53:57,840
It's the watch that his son was wearing.

751
00:53:58,560 --> 00:54:00,560
He said he got it as a gift from his father.

752
00:54:01,960 --> 00:54:03,840
I figured if I sent his son's watch,

753
00:54:04,160 --> 00:54:06,120
he might get scared and show up.

754
00:54:06,480 --> 00:54:08,800
That's why I kept it at my house.

755
00:54:09,800 --> 00:54:12,480
But how do you have this?

756
00:54:13,400 --> 00:54:14,760
Who's the guy's father?

757
00:54:16,640 --> 00:54:18,120
Woo Byung Sik.

758
00:54:21,440 --> 00:54:24,800
Woo Byung Sik, the man who killed my son.

759
00:54:32,120 --> 00:54:33,160
He's...

760
00:54:33,720 --> 00:54:35,440
The building owner, Woo Byung Sik,

761
00:54:36,200 --> 00:54:38,840
tried to flee abroad with all related documents.

762
00:54:38,840 --> 00:54:40,080
But he got into a rollover accident...

763
00:54:40,680 --> 00:54:42,080
on his way to the airport...

764
00:54:43,400 --> 00:54:45,560
and was found completely burnt.

765
00:54:46,720 --> 00:54:48,680
("A Body Speculated to Be Woo Byung Sik Has Been Found")

766
00:54:51,680 --> 00:54:53,200
I thought this guy was dead.

767
00:54:53,680 --> 00:54:55,720
He's not dead.

768
00:54:57,200 --> 00:54:59,400
Everyone just thinks he's dead.

769
00:55:00,320 --> 00:55:01,400
No.

770
00:55:01,960 --> 00:55:04,400
Everybody knows that he's still alive,

771
00:55:04,520 --> 00:55:06,400
but they're just pretending like they don't know!

772
00:55:31,200 --> 00:55:32,560
Mr. Park didn't come back,

773
00:55:33,160 --> 00:55:34,720
and her cousin left a while ago.

774
00:55:36,920 --> 00:55:37,960
Why?

775
00:55:38,160 --> 00:55:39,360
Woo Byung Sik.

776
00:55:40,360 --> 00:55:41,840
Woo Byung Sik's still alive.

777
00:55:42,640 --> 00:55:44,960
This watch. It's the exact same watch that I saw.

778
00:55:46,520 --> 00:55:48,760
Ms. Fortune-teller. Ms. Fortune-teller.

779
00:55:49,080 --> 00:55:51,160
While everyone was being fooled,

780
00:55:54,160 --> 00:55:55,560
my wife...

781
00:55:57,000 --> 00:55:58,520
My poor wife...

782
00:55:58,920 --> 00:56:00,600
refused to give up.

783
00:56:00,840 --> 00:56:02,280
I thought she deserved to die.

784
00:56:03,520 --> 00:56:06,560
I was cursing at her for betraying our son by getting dirty money.

785
00:56:06,880 --> 00:56:11,080
But she was actually fighting for Seung Chul all by herself.

786
00:56:12,520 --> 00:56:14,040
And I didn't even know that.

787
00:56:18,000 --> 00:56:21,040
- Please just die already! Just die! - Stop it!

788
00:56:21,280 --> 00:56:22,880
Just die already!

789
00:56:30,360 --> 00:56:31,520
What?

790
00:56:32,720 --> 00:56:33,960
This...

791
00:56:35,280 --> 00:56:36,360
This is...

792
00:56:40,320 --> 00:56:44,400
This box was with Soon Hee's other belongings from the Philippines.

793
00:56:45,160 --> 00:56:47,600
And I think she was going to send it to you.

794
00:56:50,240 --> 00:56:51,240
(To Seung Chul's dad)

795
00:56:56,920 --> 00:56:58,280
Honey.

796
00:56:58,800 --> 00:57:00,680
You resented me a lot, didn't you?

